<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-88-0865 </DOCNO><TEXT>The manual is designed for the plant manager or others with the abilityto initiate corporate investment decisions. It is not intended exclusivelyfor the expert engineer or attorney, although both might benefit fromit. Rather, the manual provides the manager with detailed, timely andunderstandable materials which might serve as the basis of a cogenerationfeasibility study. The book is divided into the following five sections:regulation of cogeneration and small power production; cogeneration andthe environment; engineering and cogeneration; cogeneration contracts;and finance and cogeneration. Eighteen major subsections have been abstractedseparately for inclusion on the Energy Data Base.</TEXT></DOC>